descriptionNullable:
Questions, answers, and metadata collected from 17,685 Multidimensional Sexual Self-Concept Questionnaires. The data was hosted on OpenPsychometrics.org a nonprofit effort to educate the public about psychology and to collect data for psychological research. Their notes on the data collected in the codebook.txt
> Sexual self-concept is a persons own view of their sexual behaviours and actions.

> The MSSCQ was created by Dr. William E. Snell, Jr. in 1995 for the general study of sexuality. It measures along twenty separate scales.
